<item>
            <title>[LU-17761] sanity-compr test_cleanup: FAIL: test_sanity failed with 1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17761</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While running &lt;tt&gt;sanity-compr&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;tt&gt;test_sanity()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;test_sanityn()&lt;/tt&gt;, if there was sub-subtest failure, then the &lt;tt&gt;test_cleanup&lt;/tt&gt; would be incorrectly marked as FAIL.&lt;br/&gt;
We should leave it to the individual sanity/sanityn subtests to mark their failures, &lt;tt&gt;test_sanity()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;test_sanityn()&lt;/tt&gt; should not also return an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
